OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Civil rights campaigner Roy Hackett,   
OL,6, described as a "humble freedom         
OL,7, fighter", has died at the age of 93.   
OL,9,FMr Hackett was one of the organisers of
OL,10,Fthe Bristol Bus Boycott, a successful  
OL,11,Fcampaign to overturn a ban by Bristol  
OL,12,FOmnibus Company on employing black and 
OL,13,FAsian drivers and conductors.          
OL,15,FHe once said: "I lived in many places  
OL,16,Fbefore I came to Bristol, and I never  
OL,17,Fhad racism as tough as back then."     
OL,19,FBorn in Jamaica, he was appointed an   
OL,20,FMBE in 2009 and an OBE in 2020.        
